<h2>Resources</h2>
<p>
The Resource tool is used to make resources for school, such as school materials or class rooms.
</p>
<h3>Using the Resource tool</h3>

<!-- 
below are the steps that I explain
--> 
<ol>

<li> <!-- step 1 -->
Go to the <b>Actions</b> "drag down" bar and drag down to <b>New Resources</b>.
</li>
<br/>
<li> <!-- step 2 -->
In the next screen, you will see a text box with the name "Title" on the left of it.<br/>
You would type the name of the resource in the box. Here is an example:<br/>
<div class="example" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,100); font-family: sans-serif; border: thin solid #000000;">
<br/>
&nbsp;Title&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text_box"  style ="      background-color: rgb(255,255,255); font-family: sans-serif; border: thin solid #000000">blackboard&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
<br/><br/>
</div>
</li>
<br/>
<li> <!-- step 3 -->
In the next step, you will see the word "Description" and a large text box right below it.<br/>
In the text box, you will type the description of the resource from the previous step. Here is an example:
<div class="example" style="background-color: rgb(255,255,100); font-family: sans-serif; border: thin solid #000000;">
<br/>

&nbsp;Description<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="text_box" style ="background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-family: sans-serif;border: thin solid #000000">
The backboard is used to write multiple things for people to see, such as announcements and lessons.
</span>

<br/><br/>
</div>
</li>
<br/>
<li> <!-- step 4 -->
In this step, you will see the word "Location" and a checkbox. You will check the checkbox if the resource is a location, like a classroom.
</li>
<br/>
<li> <!-- step 5 -->

</li>
</ol>
